name: tiger-line-shapefile-2014-series-information-file-for-the-point-landmark-state-based-
notes:
The Census
               Bureau includes landmarks in the MTDB for locating special features and to help
               enumerators during field operations. Some of the more common landmark types include
               area landmarks such as airports, cemeteries, parks, mountain peaks/summits, schools,
               and churches and other religious institutions. The Census Bureau has added landmark
               features to MTDB on an as-needed basis and made no attempt to ensure that all
               instances of a particular feature were included. The presence or absence of a
               landmark such as a hospital or prison does not mean that the living quarters
               associated with that landmark were geocoded to that census tabulation block or
               excluded from the census enumeration.
